ANNUITY WIRES




Allianz Life To Launch New Variable Annuity


June 2010
BY:

Recently, Allianz Life Insurance Company
of North America announced plans
to offer a new variable annuity product,
the Allianz Retirement Pro Variable
Annuity, later this year.
Allianz plans to break into the feebased
market with the creation of this
new product that's specifically for the
market's dually registered investment
advisors. As a long-term financial vehicle,
Allianz Retirement Pro features flexible
protection, low-cost tax deferral and ability
to allocate or transfer funds between
two accounts. Depending on the investors'
objectives, they can move money
between an account with an extensive
investment lineup that offers more
equity exposure (the Base Account) and
an account that offers income and death
benefit guarantees (the Income Advantage
Account). Allianz said this product
will offer fee-based advisors' clients
an insured solution that will assist them
with accumulating, preserving and distributing
retirement assets.





